missing_systems_instructions.step:
The Word doc explicitly states Legacy Score should be calculated by a Supabase DB trigger,
not by client-side code. Add this to supabase/patch_lore.sql:
  CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION update_legacy_score()
  RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
  BEGIN
    UPDATE profiles
    SET legacy_score = legacy_score + (
      SELECT legacy_pts FROM figures WHERE id = NEW.figure_id
    )
    WHERE user_id = NEW.user_id;
    RETURN NEW;
  END;
  $$ LANGUAGE plpgsql SECURITY DEFINER;

  CREATE TRIGGER on_capture_update_score
  AFTER INSERT ON user_captures
  FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION update_legacy_score();
After adding this trigger, remove the client-side DB.Profiles.addLegacyPoints() call
that happens after figure capture — the trigger handles it server-side.
Keep the client call ONLY for lore points (lore_nodes don't have a capture trigger).
